# Firebase Configuration (Expo/React Native)
# Get these values from your Firebase project settings
# https://console.firebase.google.com/

# IMPORTANT: In Expo, environment variables must be prefixed with EXPO_PUBLIC_
# to be accessible in the client-side code.

# Firebase API Key
EXPO_PUBLIC_FIREBASE_API_KEY=your-api-key-here

# Firebase Auth Domain
EXPO_PUBLIC_FIREBASE_AUTH_DOMAIN=your-project-id.firebaseapp.com

# Firebase Project ID
EXPO_PUBLIC_FIREBASE_PROJECT_ID=your-project-id

# Firebase Storage Bucket
EXPO_PUBLIC_FIREBASE_STORAGE_BUCKET=your-project-id.appspot.com

# Firebase Messaging Sender ID
EXPO_PUBLIC_FIREBASE_MESSAGING_SENDER_ID=your-sender-id

# Firebase App ID
EXPO_PUBLIC_FIREBASE_APP_ID=your-app-id

# Google OAuth
# EXPO_PUBLIC_GOOGLE_WEB_CLIENT_ID=123456789-xxxxx.apps.googleusercontent.com

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Setup Instructions:
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
#
# 1. Copy this file to .env:
#    cp environment.example .env
#
# 2. Replace all placeholder values with your actual Firebase credentials
#
# 3. To get your Firebase credentials:
#    - Go to Firebase Console: https://console.firebase.google.com/
#    - Select your project (or create a new one)
#    - Go to Project Settings > General > Your apps
#    - If you haven't added an app yet, click "Add app" and select Web
#    - Copy the configuration values from the Firebase SDK snippet
#
# 4. For Google Sign-In on mobile:
#    - Go to Google Cloud Console: https://console.cloud.google.com/
#    - Enable Google Sign-In API
#    - Configure OAuth consent screen
#    - Create OAuth 2.0 credentials for Android and/or iOS
#
# 5. Run the app:
#    npm run start
#
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
